glosses: to lug, tug, drag along the ground

etymology:
From Ottoman Turkish سورومك (sürümek, “to drag”), from Proto-Turkic *südre- (“to pull, tug”).
Akin to Proto-Mongolic *sidur-, compare Mongolian шудрах (šudrax, “to pull forward”). Medial /d/ was lost instead of yielding /y/, compare a similar case at üremek.
Cognates
Cognate with Azerbaijani sürümək (“to drag”), Bashkir һөйрәү (höyrəw, “to pull, drag”), Chuvash сӗтӗрме (sĕt̬ĕrme, “to drag, pull”), Khakas сӧзірерге (sözìrerge, “to pull, drag”), Kazakh сүйреу (süireu, “to drag”), Kyrgyz сүйрөө (süyröö, “to drag”), Southern Altai сӱӱртеер (süürteer, “to drag”), Tatar сөйрәү (söyräw, “to pull, drag”), Turkmen süýremek (“to pull out, drag”), Tuvan сөдүртүр (södürtür, “to drag”), Uzbek sudramoq (“to drag, pull”), Yakut өтүү (ötüü, “belt for fastening loads”).
